article.headline: S. Illinois 38, S. Dakota State 35
article.story: CARBONDALE, Ill. -- Kyle Dougherty completed a 28-yard field goal with less than 3 minutes left to lead Southern Illinois to a 38-35 victory over South Dakota State on Saturday. South Dakota State (6-5, 5-2 Summit League) tied the game at the end of the third period with a touchdown off a 1-yard run from Kyle Minett. Minett led South Dakota State with a pair of touchdowns and 90 yards. Southern Illinois (8-2, 6-1 Missouri Valley Football Conference) won despite having fewer offensive yards, 383 to 347 for South Dakota State. Chris Dieker passed for 245 yards and one touchdown for the Salukis, who earned two touchdowns off big plays. Larry Warner had a touchdown from a 89-yard kickoff return and Marty Rodgers ran 57 yards after an interception to score. Dougherty completed five extra point kicks for Southern Illinois. Ryan Berry threw for 286 yards and three touchdowns South Dakota State. The Jackrabbits kept their scoring steady, mostly off single-yards runs. The Jackrabbits didn't try for any field goals. Southern Illinois led 35-21 going into the break. South Dakota State came back in the third period to score 14 unanswered points and tie the game.
